Message: The user completes the submission of the form

My ad was recently rejected due to a reported issue with the landing page URL not working. However, I’ve verified that the link is functioning correctly, and we’re seeing active users on our website through Google Analytics.

Could you kindly review the following URL and confirm its status?

I'm sorry to hear about the issue with your ad rejection. While I can't directly review URLs, I recommend checking the URL format to ensure there are no capital letters in the 'http://' or 'https://' prefix, as this can sometimes cause issues. If you believe your ad complies with our policies and the rejection was a misunderstanding, you can submit an appeal by emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com. For more details on handling ad rejections, please refer to this article: [My ad got rejected. What's next?](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18085960681101-My-ad-got-rejected-What-s-next). Let me know if there's anything else I can assist you with!
I'm here to help with whatever you need! Let me know your question, and I'll do my best to assist you right away. If you need further assistance, feel free to email adsupport@newsbreak.com.
